entries.title: Putin Thanks Church for Supporting Ukraine Invasion in Christmas Message
entries.description: Russia’s president marked the first Orthodox Christmas since he launched his full-scale war, while the head of the church in Moscow said the conflict was a struggle “to keep human civilization viable.”

entries.title: Iran Executes Two Protesters Accused of Killing Militia Member
entries.description: The two men hanged were the third and fourth Iranians known to have received the death penalty in connection with the country’s nearly four-month-old antigovernment demonstrations.

entries.title: Fighting Rages in Ukraine on Orthodox Christmas Despite Putin's Call for Truce
entries.description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky welcomed the largest package of military aid from the U.S. and its allies as “timely and strong.”
